doctype html
html
  head
    meta(charset="utf-8")
    meta(content="IE=edge,chrome=1" http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible")
    meta(content="width=device-width, user-scalable=no", name="viewport")
    title= page_title
    link(rel="stylesheet", href="/stylesheets/default.css")
    link(rel="prefetch" href="/images/status/idle.png")
    link(rel="prefetch" href="/images/status/in-progress.png")
    link(rel="prefetch" href="/images/status/error.png")
    script(src="/scripts/jquery.min.js")
    script(src="/scripts/client.js")
  body
    block content
    #info-panel
        h1 #{description}
        p Seen those luggage lockers at the railway station? Itâ€™s like that, but for files.
        section
            h2 Simple
            p Tag your locker, select a file from your device, and enter a passphrase.
            p To retrieve a stored file, go to <br><strong>#{domain}/your_tag</strong> and enter your passphrase.
        section
            h2 Private
            p Lockers are anonymous and passphrase protected. No personal information is required or collected.
            p Files put in lockers are encrypted on your device before being sent securely to the server.
        section
            h2 Open Source
            p #{app_name} is Free and Open Source software. You can see the <a href="#{repo_url}" target="blank">source code</a> and even run your own instance.
            p Questions or comments?<br>Contact <a href="#{admin_contact_info}" target="_blank">#{admin_name}</a>.
        a(href="") Aha. Cheers, thanks.
    footer
        a#logo(href="/", target="_blank")
            img(src="/images/logo/logo-inverted.png" alt="#{page_title}")
        nav
            button Go To Locker
            form#locker-go-to(autocomplete="off")
                fieldset.bubble
                    span #{domain}/
                    input(type="text", maxlength="24")
                    input(type="submit", value="Go", disabled="disabled")
        #tagline #{description} <a href="">I beg your pardon?</a>
        a#artist(href="http://planetpeanut.uk/", target="_blank") Cover by &nbsp;<span>Hylke Bons</span>
